==English==
===Etymology===
From French ''[[bœuf]]'' (ox); presumably from Latin ''[[bos]]'' (ox).

===Noun===
'''beef''' (plural: '''[[beeves]]''', '''[[beef]]''', or '''[[beefs]]''')

#''(uncountable)'' The [[meat]] from a [[cow]], [[bull]] or other [[bovine]].
#:''I hate eating '''beef'''.''
#''(countable, plural '''beef''' or '''beeves''')'' (''archaic'') A generic term for a cow or bull.  
#:''Do you want to raise '''beefs'''?''
#''(countable, plural '''beefs''')'' a [[complaint]] or [[disagreement]]
#:''He has a '''beef''' with anyone who tells him otherwise.''

